{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Repeal the Hong Kong Economic Trade Office Act 1996",
        "additional_details": "Hong Kong\u2019s Economic and Trade Office was granted diplomatic privileges and immunities by the Act in 1996 ahead of the city's handover from Britain to China, recognising promised autonomy under \u201cone country, two systems.\u201d Since the 2020 National Security Law, that autonomy has ended.\r\n\r\nThe UK Government says China has undermined the \u201cone country, two systems\u201d and the Sino-British Joint Declaration, a legally binding treaty, while Beijing insists Hong Kong is fully part of China. We believe the basis for the office no longer exists, so it should be closed.",
        "background": "Pass legislation to close the Hong Kong Economic Trade Office in light of the lack of autonomy Hong Kong now has from Beijing, by introducing legislation to repeal the Hong Kong Economic Trade Office Act 1996 through, for example, a Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office (Revocation) Act 2026.",
        "closed_at": null,
